defs.docs: RustType is a pure Rust alternative to libraries like FreeType.

defs.name: Point
defs.docs: A point in 2-dimensional space, with each dimension of type `N`.

defs.name: Vector
defs.docs: A vector in 2-dimensional space, with each dimension of type `N`.

defs.name: point
defs.docs: A convenience function for generating `Point`s.

defs.name: vector
defs.docs: A convenience function for generating `Vector`s.

defs.name: Line
defs.docs: A straight line between two points, `p[0]` and `p[1]`

defs.name: Curve
defs.docs: A quadratic Bezier curve, starting at `p[0]`, ending at `p[2]`, with control point `p[1]`.

defs.name: Rect
defs.docs: A rectangle, with top-left corner at `min`, and bottom-right corner at `max`.

defs.name: BTreeMap
defs.docs: A map based on a B-Tree.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over a BTreeMap's entries.

defs.name: IterMut
defs.docs: A mutable iterator over a BTreeMap's entries.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: An owning iterator over a BTreeMap's entries.

defs.name: Keys
defs.docs: An iterator over a BTreeMap's keys.

defs.name: Values
defs.docs: An iterator over a BTreeMap's values.

defs.name: Range
defs.docs: An iterator over a sub-range of BTreeMap's entries.

defs.name: RangeMut
defs.docs: A mutable iterator over a sub-range of BTreeMap's entries.

defs.name: Vacant
defs.docs: A vacant Entry

defs.name: Occupied
defs.docs: An occupied Entry

defs.name: Entry
defs.docs: A view into a single entry in a map, which may either be vacant or occupied.

defs.name: VacantEntry
defs.docs: A vacant Entry.

defs.name: OccupiedEntry
defs.docs: An occupied Entry.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Makes a new empty BTreeMap with a reasonable choice for B.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears the map, removing all values.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the value corresponding to the key.

defs.name: contains_key
defs.docs: Returns true if the map contains a value for the specified key.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Returns a mutable reference to the value corresponding to the key.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, key: K, value: V) -> Option<V>
defs.docs: Inserts a key-value pair into the map.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs:
Removes a key from the map, returning the value at the key if the key
 was previously in the map.

defs.name: range
defs.value: fn <Min, Max> (&self, min: Bound<&Min>, max: Bound<&Max>) -> Range<K, V>
defs.docs:
Constructs a double-ended iterator over a sub-range of elements in the map, starting
 at min, and ending at max. If min is `Unbounded`, then it will be treated as "negative
 infinity", and if max is `Unbounded`, then it will be treated as "positive infinity".
 Thus range(Unbounded, Unbounded) will yield the whole collection.

defs.name: range_mut
defs.value: fn <Min, Max> (&mut self, min: Bound<&Min>, max: Bound<&Max>) -> RangeMut<K, V>
defs.docs:
Constructs a mutable double-ended iterator over a sub-range of elements in the map, starting
 at min, and ending at max. If min is `Unbounded`, then it will be treated as "negative
 infinity", and if max is `Unbounded`, then it will be treated as "positive infinity".
 Thus range(Unbounded, Unbounded) will yield the whole collection.

defs.name: entry
defs.value: fn (&mut self, key: K) -> Entry<K, V>
defs.docs: Gets the given key's corresponding entry in the map for in-place manipulation.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Gets an iterator over the entries of the map, sorted by key.

defs.name: iter_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable iterator over the entries of the map, sorted by key.

defs.name: keys
defs.docs: Gets an iterator over the keys of the map, in sorted order.

defs.name: values
defs.docs: Gets an iterator over the values of the map, in order by key.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements in the map.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if the map contains no elements.

defs.name: or_insert
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the default if empty, and returns
 a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: or_insert_with
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the result of the default function if empty,
 and returns a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs:
Sets the value of the entry with the VacantEntry's key,
 and returns a mutable reference to it.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: into_mut
defs.docs: Converts the entry into a mutable reference to its value.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs:
Sets the value of the entry with the OccupiedEntry's key,
 and returns the entry's old value.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Takes the value of the entry out of the map, and returns it.

defs.name: BTreeSet
defs.docs: A set based on a B-Tree.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over a BTreeSet's items.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: An owning iterator over a BTreeSet's items.

defs.name: Range
defs.docs: An iterator over a sub-range of BTreeSet's items.

defs.name: Difference
defs.docs: A lazy iterator producing elements in the set difference (in-order).

defs.name: SymmetricDifference
defs.docs: A lazy iterator producing elements in the set symmetric difference (in-order).

defs.name: Intersection
defs.docs: A lazy iterator producing elements in the set intersection (in-order).

defs.name: Union
defs.docs: A lazy iterator producing elements in the set union (in-order).

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Makes a new BTreeSet with a reasonable choice of B.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Gets an iterator over the BTreeSet's contents.

defs.name: range
defs.value: fn <'a, Min, Max> (&'a self, min: Bound<&Min>, max: Bound<&Max>) -> Range<'a, T>
defs.docs:
Constructs a double-ended iterator over a sub-range of elements in the set, starting
 at min, and ending at max. If min is `Unbounded`, then it will be treated as "negative
 infinity", and if max is `Unbounded`, then it will be treated as "positive infinity".
 Thus range(Unbounded, Unbounded) will yield the whole collection.

defs.name: difference
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, other: &'a BTreeSet<T>) -> Difference<'a, T>
defs.docs: Visits the values representing the difference, in ascending order.

defs.name: symmetric_difference
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, other: &'a BTreeSet<T>) -> SymmetricDifference<'a, T>
defs.docs: Visits the values representing the symmetric difference, in ascending order.

defs.name: intersection
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, other: &'a BTreeSet<T>) -> Intersection<'a, T>
defs.docs: Visits the values representing the intersection, in ascending order.

defs.name: union
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, other: &'a BTreeSet<T>) -> Union<'a, T>
defs.docs: Visits the values representing the union, in ascending order.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements in the set.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if the set contains no elements.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears the set, removing all values.

defs.name: contains
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the set contains a value.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the value in the set, if any, that is equal to the given value.

defs.name: is_disjoint
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if the set has no elements in common with `other`.
 This is equivalent to checking for an empty intersection.

defs.name: is_subset
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the set is a subset of another.

defs.name: is_superset
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the set is a superset of another.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs: Adds a value to the set.

defs.name: replace
defs.docs:
Adds a value to the set, replacing the existing value, if any, that is equal to the given
 one. Returns the replaced value.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs:
Removes a value from the set. Returns `true` if the value was
 present in the set.

defs.name: take
defs.docs: Removes and returns the value in the set, if any, that is equal to the given one.

defs.name: Included
defs.docs: An inclusive bound.

defs.name: Excluded
defs.docs: An exclusive bound.

defs.name: Unbounded
defs.docs: An infinite endpoint. Indicates that there is no bound in this direction.

defs.name: gpu_cache
defs.docs:
This module provides capabilities for managing a cache of rendered glyphs in GPU memory, with the goal of
 minimisng the size and frequency of glyph uploads to GPU memory from the CPU.

defs.name: Cache
defs.docs: An implementation of a dynamic GPU glyph cache. See the module documentation for more information.

defs.name: GlyphNotCached
defs.docs: Indicates that the requested glyph is not present in the cache

defs.name: CacheReadErr
defs.docs: Returned from `Cache::rect_for`.

defs.name: GlyphTooLarge
defs.docs: At least one of the queued glyphs is too big to fit into the cache, even if all other glyphs are removed.

defs.name: NoRoomForWholeQueue
defs.docs:
Not all of the requested glyphs can fit into the cache, even if the cache is completely cleared before
 the attempt.

defs.name: CacheWriteErr
defs.docs: Returned from `Cache::cache_queued`.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (width: u32, height: u32, scale_tolerance: f32, position_tolerance: f32) -> Cache
defs.docs:
Constructs a new cache. Note that this is just the CPU side of the cache. The GPU texture is managed
 by the user.

defs.name: set_scale_tolerance
defs.docs: Sets the scale tolerance for the cache. See the documentation for `Cache::new` for more information.

defs.name: scale_tolerance
defs.docs: Returns the current scale tolerance for the cache.

defs.name: set_position_tolerance
defs.docs:
Sets the subpixel position tolerance for the cache. See the documentation for `Cache::new` for more
 information.

defs.name: position_tolerance
defs.docs: Returns the current subpixel position tolerance for the cache.

defs.name: dimensions
defs.docs:
Returns the cache texture dimensions assumed by the cache. For proper operation this should
 match the dimensions of the used GPU texture.

defs.name: queue_glyph
defs.value: fn (&mut self, font_id: usize, glyph: PositionedGlyph) -> ()
defs.docs:
Queue a glyph for caching by the next call to `cache_queued`. `font_id` is used to
 disambiguate glyphs from different fonts. The user should ensure that `font_id` is unique to the
 font the glyph is from.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears the cache. Does not affect the glyph queue.

defs.name: clear_queue
defs.docs: Clears the glyph queue.

defs.name: cache_queued
defs.value: fn <F> (&mut self, mut uploader: F) -> Result<(), CacheWriteErr>
defs.docs:
Caches the queued glyphs. If this is unsuccessful, the queue is untouched.
 Any glyphs cached by previous calls to this function may be removed from the cache to make
 room for the newly queued glyphs. Thus if you want to ensure that a glyph is in the cache,
 the most recently cached queue must have contained that glyph.

defs.name: rect_for
defs.value: fn <'a> (&'a self, font_id: usize, glyph: &PositionedGlyph) -> Result<Option<(Rect<f32>, Rect<i32>)>, CacheReadErr>
defs.docs:
Retrieves the (floating point) texture coordinates of the quad for a glyph in the cache,
 as well as the pixel-space (integer) coordinates that this region should be drawn at.
 In the majority of cases these pixel-space coordinates should be identical to the bounding box of the
 input glyph. They only differ if the cache has returned a substitute glyph that is deemed close enough
 to the requested glyph as specified by the cache tolerance parameters.

defs.name: FontCollection
defs.docs:
A collection of fonts read straight from a font file's data. The data in the collection is not validated.
 This structure may or may not own the font data.

defs.name: Font
defs.docs: A single font. This may or may not own the font data.

defs.name: SharedBytes
defs.docs:
`SharedBytes` handles the lifetime of font data used in RustType. The data is either a shared
 reference to externally owned data, or managed by reference counting. `SharedBytes` can be
 conveniently used with `From` and `Into`, and dereferences to the contained bytes.

defs.name: Codepoint
defs.docs: Represents a Unicode code point.

defs.name: CodepointOrGlyphId
defs.docs: Represents either a Unicode code point, or a glyph identifier for a font.

defs.name: GlyphId
defs.docs:
Represents a glyph identifier for a particular font. This identifier will not necessarily correspond to
 the correct glyph in a font other than the one that it was obtained from.

defs.name: Glyph
defs.docs:
A single glyph of a font. this may either be a thin wrapper referring to the font and the glyph id, or
 it may be a standalone glyph that owns the data needed by it.

defs.name: HMetrics
defs.docs:
The "horizontal metrics" of a glyph. This is useful for calculating the horizontal offset of a glyph
 from the previous one in a string when laying a string out horizontally.

defs.name: advance_width
defs.docs: The horizontal offset that the origin of the next glyph should be from the origin of this glyph.

defs.name: left_side_bearing
defs.docs: The horizontal offset between the origin of this glyph and the leftmost edge/point of the glyph.

defs.name: VMetrics
defs.docs:
The "vertical metrics" of a font at a particular scale. This is useful for calculating the amount of
 vertical space to give a line of text, and for computing the vertical offset between successive lines.

defs.name: ascent
defs.docs: The highest point that any glyph in the font extends to above the baseline. Typically positive.

defs.name: descent
defs.docs: The lowest point that any glyph in the font extends to below the baseline. Typically negative.

defs.name: line_gap
defs.docs:
The gap to leave between the descent of one line and the ascent of the next. This is of
 course only a guideline given by the font's designers.

defs.name: ScaledGlyph
defs.docs:
A glyph augmented with scaling information. You can query such a glyph for information that depends
 on the scale of the glyph.

defs.name: PositionedGlyph
defs.docs:
A glyph augmented with positioning and scaling information. You can query such a glyph for information
 that depends on the scale and position of the glyph.

defs.name: Scale
defs.docs:
Defines the size of a rendered face of a font, in pixels, horizontally and vertically. A vertical
 scale of `y` pixels means that the distance betwen the ascent and descent lines (see `VMetrics`) of the
 face will be `y` pixels. If `x` and `y` are equal the scaling is uniform. Non-uniform scaling by a factor
 *f* in the horizontal direction is achieved by setting `x` equal to *f* times `y`.

defs.name: x
defs.docs: Horizontal scale, in pixels.

defs.name: y
defs.docs: Vertical scale, in pixels.

defs.name: uniform
defs.docs: Uniform scaling, equivalent to `Scale { x: s, y: s }`.

defs.name: from_bytes
defs.docs:
Constructs a font collection from an array of bytes, typically loaded from a font file.
 This array may be owned (e.g. `Vec<u8>`), or borrowed (`&[u8]`).
 As long as `From<T>` is implemented for `Bytes` for some type `T`, `T` can be used as input.

defs.name: into_font
defs.docs:
In the common case that a font collection consists of only one font, this function
 consumes this font collection and turns it into a font. If this is not the case,
 or the font is not valid (read: not supported by this library), `None` is returned.

defs.name: font_at
defs.docs:
Gets the font at index `i` in the font collection, if it exists and is valid.
 The produced font borrows the font data that is either borrowed or owned by this font collection.

defs.name: into_fonts
defs.docs: Converts `self` into an `Iterator` yielding each `Font` that exists within the collection.

defs.name: v_metrics
defs.docs:
The "vertical metrics" for this font at a given scale. These metrics are shared by all of the glyphs
 in the font.
 See `VMetrics` for more detail.

defs.name: glyph_count
defs.docs:
The number of glyphs present in this font. Glyph identifiers for this font will always be in the range
 `0..self.glyph_count()`

defs.name: glyph
defs.docs:
Returns the corresponding glyph for a Unicode code point or a glyph id for this font.
 If id corresponds to a glyph identifier, the identifier must be valid (smaller than `self.glyph_count()`),
 otherwise `None` is returned.

defs.name: glyphs_for
defs.docs: A convenience function.

defs.name: layout
defs.value: fn <'b, 'c> (&'b self, s: &'c str, scale: Scale, start: Point<f32>) -> LayoutIter<'b, 'c>
defs.docs:
A convenience function for laying out glyphs for a string horizontally. It does not take control
 characters like line breaks into account, as treatment of these is likely to depend on the application.

defs.name: pair_kerning
defs.value: fn <A, B> (&self, scale: Scale, first: A, second: B) -> f32
defs.docs: Returns additional kerning to apply as well as that given by HMetrics for a particular pair of glyphs.

defs.name: font
defs.docs:
The font to which this glyph belongs. If the glyph is a standalone glyph that owns its resources,
 it no longer has a reference to the font which it was created from (using `standalone()`). In which
 case, `None` is returned.

defs.name: id
defs.docs: The glyph identifier for this glyph.

defs.name: scaled
defs.docs:
Augments this glyph with scaling information, making methods that depend on the scale of the glyph
 available.

defs.name: standalone
defs.docs:
Turns a `Glyph<'a>` into a `Glyph<'static>`. This produces a glyph that owns its resources,
 extracted from the font. This glyph can outlive the font that it comes from.

defs.name: Segment
defs.docs: Part of a `Contour`, either a `Line` or a `Curve`.

defs.name: Contour
defs.docs: A closed loop consisting of a sequence of `Segment`s.

defs.name: id
defs.docs: The glyph identifier for this glyph.

defs.name: font
defs.docs:
The font to which this glyph belongs. If the glyph is a standalone glyph that owns its resources,
 it no longer has a reference to the font which it was created from (using `standalone()`). In which
 case, `None` is returned.

defs.name: into_unscaled
defs.docs: A reference to this glyph without the scaling

defs.name: unscaled
defs.docs: Removes the scaling from this glyph

defs.name: positioned
defs.docs:
Augments this glyph with positioning information, making methods that depend on the position of the
 glyph available.

defs.name: h_metrics
defs.docs: Retrieves the "horizontal metrics" of this glyph. See `HMetrics` for more detail.

defs.name: shape
defs.docs:
Produces a list of the contours that make up the shape of this glyph. Each contour consists of
 a sequence of segments. Each segment is either a straight `Line` or a `Curve`.

defs.name: exact_bounding_box
defs.docs:
The bounding box of the shape of this glyph, not to be confused with `pixel_bounding_box`, the
 conservative pixel-boundary bounding box. The coordinates are relative to the glyph's origin.

defs.name: standalone
defs.docs:
Constructs a glyph that owns its data from this glyph. This is similar to `Glyph::standalone`. See
 that function for more details.

defs.name: id
defs.docs: The glyph identifier for this glyph.

defs.name: font
defs.docs:
The font to which this glyph belongs. If the glyph is a standalone glyph that owns its resources,
 it no longer has a reference to the font which it was created from (using `standalone()`). In which
 case, `None` is returned.

defs.name: unpositioned
defs.docs: A reference to this glyph without positioning

defs.name: into_unpositioned
defs.docs: Removes the positioning from this glyph

defs.name: pixel_bounding_box
defs.docs:
The conservative pixel-boundary bounding box for this glyph. This is the smallest rectangle
 aligned to pixel boundaries that encloses the shape of this glyph at this position.

defs.name: shape
defs.docs: Similar to `ScaledGlyph::shape()`, but with the position of the glyph taken into account.

defs.name: draw
defs.docs: Rasterises this glyph. For each pixel in the rect given by `pixel_bounding_box()`, `o` is called:

defs.name: standalone
defs.docs:
Constructs a glyph that owns its data from this glyph. This is similar to `Glyph::standalone`. See
 that function for more details.
